31void JSHeapBroker::AttachLocalIsolateForMaglev(
32 maglev::MaglevCompilationInfo* info, LocalIsolate* local_isolate) {
33 DCHECK_NULL(local_isolate_);
34 local_isolate_ = local_isolate;
35 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(local_isolate_);
36 local_isolate_->heap()->AttachPersistentHandles(
37 info->DetachPersistentHandles());
38}
39
40void JSHeapBroker::DetachLocalIsolateForMaglev(
41 maglev::MaglevCompilationInfo* info) {
42 DCHECK_NULL(ph_);
43 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(local_isolate_);
44 std::unique_ptr<PersistentHandles> ph =
45 local_isolate_->heap()->DetachPersistentHandles();
46 local_isolate_ = nullptr;
47 info->set_persistent_handles(std::move(ph));
48}

58// LocalIsolateScope encapsulates the phase where persistent handles are
59// attached to the LocalHeap inside {local_isolate}.
60class V8_NODISCARD LocalIsolateScope final {
61 public:
62 explicit LocalIsolateScope(MaglevCompilationInfo* info,
63 LocalIsolate* local_isolate)
64 : info_(info) {
65 info_->broker()->AttachLocalIsolateForMaglev(info_, local_isolate);
66 }
67
68 ~LocalIsolateScope() { info_->broker()->DetachLocalIsolateForMaglev(info_); }
69
70 private:
71 MaglevCompilationInfo* const info_;
72};

93MaglevPipelineStatistics* CreatePipelineStatistics(
94 Isolate* isolate, MaglevCompilationInfo* compilation_info,
95 compiler::ZoneStats* zone_stats) {
96 MaglevPipelineStatistics* pipeline_stats = nullptr;
97 bool tracing_enabled;
98 TRACE_EVENT_CATEGORY_GROUP_ENABLED(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.maglev"),
99 &tracing_enabled);
100 if (tracing_enabled || v8_flags.maglev_stats || v8_flags.maglev_stats_nvp) {
101 pipeline_stats = new MaglevPipelineStatistics(
102 compilation_info, isolate->GetMaglevStatistics(), zone_stats);
103 }
104 return pipeline_stats;
105}

121CompilationJob::Status MaglevCompilationJob::PrepareJobImpl(Isolate* isolate) {
122 BeginPhaseKind("V8.MaglevPrepareJob");
123 if (info()->collect_source_positions()) {
124 SharedFunctionInfo::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(
125 isolate,
126 info()->toplevel_compilation_unit()->shared_function_info().object());
127 }
128 EndPhaseKind();
129 // TODO(v8:7700): Actual return codes.
130 return CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED;
131}
132
133CompilationJob::Status MaglevCompilationJob::ExecuteJobImpl(
134 RuntimeCallStats* stats, LocalIsolate* local_isolate) {
135 BeginPhaseKind("V8.MaglevExecuteJob");
136 LocalIsolateScope scope{info(), local_isolate};
137 if (!maglev::MaglevCompiler::Compile(local_isolate, info())) {
138 return CompilationJob::FAILED;
139 }
140 EndPhaseKind();
141 // TODO(v8:7700): Actual return codes.
142 return CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED;
143}
144
145CompilationJob::Status MaglevCompilationJob::FinalizeJobImpl(Isolate* isolate) {
146 BeginPhaseKind("V8.MaglevFinalizeJob");
147 Handle<Code> code;
148 if (!maglev::MaglevCompiler::GenerateCode(isolate, info()).ToHandle(&code)) {
149 return CompilationJob::FAILED;
150 }
151 // Functions with many inline candidates are sensitive to correct call
152 // frequency feedback and should therefore not be tiered up early.
153 if (v8_flags.profile_guided_optimization &&
154 info()->could_not_inline_all_candidates()) {
155 info()->toplevel_function()->shared()->set_cached_tiering_decision(
156 CachedTieringDecision::kNormal);
157 }
158 info()->set_code(code);
159 GlobalHandleVector<Map> maps = CollectRetainedMaps(isolate, code);
160 RegisterWeakObjectsInOptimizedCode(
161 isolate, info()->broker()->target_native_context().object(), code,
162 std::move(maps));
163 EndPhaseKind();
164 return CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED;
165}
166
167GlobalHandleVector<Map> MaglevCompilationJob::CollectRetainedMaps(
168 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Code> code) {
169 if (v8_flags.maglev_build_code_on_background) {
170 return info()->code_generator()->RetainedMaps(isolate);
171 }
172 return OptimizedCompilationJob::CollectRetainedMaps(isolate, code);
173}

175void MaglevCompilationJob::DisposeOnMainThread(Isolate* isolate) {
176 // Drop canonical handles on the main thread, to avoid (in the case of
177 // background job destruction) needing to unpark the local isolate on the
178 // background thread for unregistering the identity map's strong roots.
179 DCHECK(isolate->IsCurrent());
180 info()->DetachCanonicalHandles()->Clear();
181}

201void MaglevCompilationJob::RecordCompilationStats(Isolate* isolate) const {
202 // Don't record samples from machines without high-resolution timers,
203 // as that can cause serious reporting issues. See the thread at
204 // http://g/chrome-metrics-team/NwwJEyL8odU/discussion for more details.
205 if (base::TimeTicks::IsHighResolution()) {
206 Counters* const counters = isolate->counters();
207 counters->maglev_optimize_prepare()->AddSample(
208 static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_prepare_.InMicroseconds()));
209 counters->maglev_optimize_execute()->AddSample(
210 static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_execute_.InMicroseconds()));
211 counters->maglev_optimize_finalize()->AddSample(
212 static_cast<int>(time_taken_to_finalize_.InMicroseconds()));
213 counters->maglev_optimize_total_time()->AddSample(
214 static_cast<int>(ElapsedTime().InMicroseconds()));
215 }
216 if (v8_flags.trace_opt_stats) {
217 static double compilation_time = 0.0;
218 static int compiled_functions = 0;
219 static int code_size = 0;
220
221 compilation_time += (time_taken_to_prepare_.InMillisecondsF() +
222 time_taken_to_execute_.InMillisecondsF() +
223 time_taken_to_finalize_.InMillisecondsF());
224 compiled_functions++;
225 code_size += function()->shared()->SourceSize();
226 PrintF(
227 "[maglev] Compiled: %d functions with %d byte source size in %fms.\n",
228 compiled_functions, code_size, compilation_time);
229 }
230}

232uint64_t MaglevCompilationJob::trace_id() const {
233 // Xor together the this pointer, the info pointer, and the top level
234 // function's Handle address, to try to make the id more unique on platforms
235 // where just the `this` pointer is likely to be reused.
236 return reinterpret_cast<uint64_t>(this) ^
237 reinterpret_cast<uint64_t>(info_.get()) ^
238 info_->toplevel_function().address() ^
239 info_->toplevel_function()->shared()->function_literal_id();
240}

254// The JobTask is posted to V8::GetCurrentPlatform(). It's responsible for
255// processing the incoming queue on a worker thread.
256class MaglevConcurrentDispatcher::JobTask final : public v8::JobTask {
257 public:
258 explicit JobTask(MaglevConcurrentDispatcher* dispatcher)
259 : dispatcher_(dispatcher) {}
260
261 void Run(JobDelegate* delegate) override {
262 if (incoming_queue()->IsEmpty() && destruction_queue()->IsEmpty()) {
263 return;
264 }
265 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"), "V8.MaglevTask");
266 LocalIsolate local_isolate(isolate(), ThreadKind::kBackground);
267 DCHECK(local_isolate.heap()->IsParked());
268
269 std::unique_ptr<MaglevCompilationJob> job_to_destruct;
270 while (!delegate->ShouldYield()) {
271 std::unique_ptr<MaglevCompilationJob> job;
272 if (incoming_queue()->Dequeue(&job)) {
273 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(job);
274 TRACE_EVENT_WITH_FLOW0(
275 TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"), "V8.MaglevBackground",
276 job->trace_id(),
277 TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_IN | TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_OUT);
278 RCS_SCOPE(&local_isolate,
279 RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeBackgroundMaglev);
280 CompilationJob::Status status =
281 job->ExecuteJob(local_isolate.runtime_call_stats(), &local_isolate);
282 if (status == CompilationJob::SUCCEEDED) {
283 outgoing_queue()->Enqueue(std::move(job));
284 isolate()->stack_guard()->RequestInstallMaglevCode();
285 }
286 } else if (destruction_queue()->Dequeue(&job)) {
287 // Maglev jobs aren't cheap to destruct, so destroy them here in the
288 // background thread rather than on the main thread.
289 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(job);
290 TRACE_EVENT_WITH_FLOW0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
291 "V8.MaglevDestructBackground", job->trace_id(),
292 TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_IN);
293 UnparkedScope unparked_scope(&local_isolate);
294 job.reset();
295 } else {
296 break;
297 }
298 }
299 }
300
301 size_t GetMaxConcurrency(size_t worker_count) const override {
302 size_t num_tasks =
303 incoming_queue()->size() + destruction_queue()->size() + worker_count;
304 size_t max_threads = v8_flags.concurrent_maglev_max_threads;
305 if (max_threads > 0) {
306 return std::min(max_threads, num_tasks);
307 }
308 return num_tasks;
309 }
310
311 private:
312 Isolate* isolate() const { return dispatcher_->isolate_; }
313 QueueT* incoming_queue() const { return &dispatcher_->incoming_queue_; }
314 QueueT* outgoing_queue() const { return &dispatcher_->outgoing_queue_; }
315 QueueT* destruction_queue() const { return &dispatcher_->destruction_queue_; }
316
317 MaglevConcurrentDispatcher* const dispatcher_;
318 const Handle<JSFunction> function_;
319};
320
321MaglevConcurrentDispatcher::MaglevConcurrentDispatcher(Isolate* isolate)
322 : isolate_(isolate) {
323 bool enable = v8_flags.concurrent_recompilation && maglev::IsMaglevEnabled();
324 if (enable) {
325 bool is_tracing =
326 v8_flags.print_maglev_code || v8_flags.trace_maglev_graph_building ||
327 v8_flags.trace_maglev_inlining || v8_flags.print_maglev_deopt_verbose ||
328 v8_flags.print_maglev_graph || v8_flags.print_maglev_graphs ||
329 v8_flags.trace_maglev_phi_untagging || v8_flags.trace_maglev_regalloc;
330
331 if (is_tracing) {
332 PrintF("Concurrent maglev has been disabled for tracing.\n");
333 enable = false;
334 }
335 }
336 if (enable) {
337 TaskPriority priority = v8_flags.concurrent_maglev_high_priority_threads
338 ? TaskPriority::kUserBlocking
339 : TaskPriority::kUserVisible;
340 job_handle_ = V8::GetCurrentPlatform()->PostJob(
341 priority, std::make_unique<JobTask>(this));
342 DCHECK(is_enabled());
343 } else {
344 DCHECK(!is_enabled());
345 }
346}
347
348MaglevConcurrentDispatcher::~MaglevConcurrentDispatcher() {
349 if (is_enabled() && job_handle_->IsValid()) {
350 // Wait for the job handle to complete, so that we know the queue
351 // pointers are safe.
352 job_handle_->Cancel();
353 }
354}
355
356void MaglevConcurrentDispatcher::EnqueueJob(
357 std::unique_ptr<MaglevCompilationJob>&& job) {
358 DCHECK(is_enabled());
359 incoming_queue_.Enqueue(std::move(job));
360 job_handle_->NotifyConcurrencyIncrease();
361}
362
363void MaglevConcurrentDispatcher::FinalizeFinishedJobs() {
364 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate_);
365 while (!outgoing_queue_.IsEmpty()) {
366 std::unique_ptr<MaglevCompilationJob> job;
367 outgoing_queue_.Dequeue(&job);
368 TRACE_EVENT_WITH_FLOW0(
369 TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"), "V8.MaglevConcurrentFinalize",
370 job->trace_id(), TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_IN | TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_OUT);
371 RCS_SCOPE(isolate_,
372 RuntimeCallCounterId::kOptimizeConcurrentFinalizeMaglev);
373 Compiler::FinalizeMaglevCompilationJob(job.get(), isolate_);
374 job->DisposeOnMainThread(isolate_);
375 if (v8_flags.maglev_destroy_on_background) {
376 // Maglev jobs aren't cheap to destruct, so re-enqueue them for
377 // destruction on a background thread.
378 destruction_queue_.Enqueue(std::move(job));
379 job_handle_->NotifyConcurrencyIncrease();
380 } else {
381 TRACE_EVENT_WITH_FLOW0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
382 "V8.MaglevDestruct", job->trace_id(),
383 TRACE_EVENT_FLAG_FLOW_IN);
384 job.reset();
385 }
386 }
387}
388
389void MaglevConcurrentDispatcher::AwaitCompileJobs() {
390 // Use Join to wait until there are no more queued or running jobs.
391 {
392 AllowGarbageCollection allow_before_parking;
393 isolate_->main_thread_local_isolate()->BlockMainThreadWhileParked(
394 [this]() { job_handle_->Join(); });
395 }
396 // Join kills the job handle, so drop it and post a new one.
397 TaskPriority priority = v8_flags.concurrent_maglev_high_priority_threads
398 ? TaskPriority::kUserBlocking
399 : TaskPriority::kUserVisible;
400 job_handle_ = V8::GetCurrentPlatform()->PostJob(
401 priority, std::make_unique<JobTask>(this));
402 DCHECK(incoming_queue_.IsEmpty());
403}
404
405void MaglevConcurrentDispatcher::Flush(BlockingBehavior behavior) {
406 while (!incoming_queue_.IsEmpty()) {
407 std::unique_ptr<MaglevCompilationJob> job;
408 incoming_queue_.Dequeue(&job);
409 }
410 while (!destruction_queue_.IsEmpty()) {
411 std::unique_ptr<MaglevCompilationJob> job;
412 destruction_queue_.Dequeue(&job);
413 }
414 if (behavior == BlockingBehavior::kBlock && job_handle_->IsValid()) {
415 AwaitCompileJobs();
416 }
417 while (!outgoing_queue_.IsEmpty()) {
418 std::unique_ptr<MaglevCompilationJob> job;
419 outgoing_queue_.Dequeue(&job);
420 }
421}
